  "prompt": "Do we have Financial Management in IPCC group 1 in may 2017? Websites show change in syllabus.",
  "response": "As of May 2017, **Financial Management was not included in Group I of the IPCC (Intermediate Professional Competence Course) syllabus**. Instead, Financial Management was part of **Group II**. Here's a breakdown of the IPCC syllabus around that time:\n\n### **Group I:**\n1. **Paper 1:** Accounting\n2. **Paper 2:** Corporate and Other Laws\n3. **Paper 3:** Cost and Management Accounting\n4. **Paper 4:** Taxation\n\n### **Group II:**\n1. **Paper 5:** Advanced Accounting\n2. **Paper 6:** Auditing and Assurance\n3. **Paper 7:** Information Technology and Strategic Management\n4. **Paper 8:** **Financial Management and Economics for Finance**\n\nIt's possible that recent syllabus changes on various websites have led to some confusion. To obtain the most accurate and updated information, I recommend visiting the official [Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) website](https://www.icai.org/) or contacting ICAI directly.\n\nIf you have any further questions or need clarification on other aspects of the IPCC syllabus, feel free to ask!",
